cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper is about a deep learning framework that supports multiple models and depends on OpenCV. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers topics related to machine learning, which is the core of the proposed framework.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category covers topics related to computer vision, which is one of the main applications of the proposed framework.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers topics related to artificial intelligence, which is the broader field that includes deep learning.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category covers topics related to neural networks, which are the building blocks of deep learning.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category covers topics related to natural language processing, which is another potential application of the proposed framework.
